FBIS4-17349 "drsov079_b_94034" FBIS-SOV-94-079 Daily Report 24 Apr 1994 RUSSIAN NATIONAL AFFAIRS Political Issues Calls for Yeltsin's Resignation Calls for Yeltsin's Resignation LD2404171094 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1534 GMT 24 Apr 94 LD2404171094 Moscow INTERFAX English BFN [Text] The National Council of the National Salvation Front [NSF] adopted a resolution on Sunday which says that Boris Yeltsin's resignation is the compulsory condition for signing the Civic Accord agreement. The National Council members also expressed protest against plans to hold Russian-American manoeuvres in the Orenburg Region (the Urals) and urged all patriots to join this protest. Ilya Konstantinov was elected chairman of the NSF's Executive Committee. Four more co-chairmen were elected in addition to the 17 already working: Sazhiy Umalatova, Valeriy Skurlatov, Mikhail Titov and Valeriy Smirnov.
